WEBVTT

00:01.900 --> 00:05.300
ALLISON:
 <i>Dread becomes unannounced and then consumes our feelings</i>

00:05.300 --> 00:08.000
 <i>with its irrational</i>
 <i>sense of doom.</i>

00:14.000 --> 00:16.300
 <i>Have you ever had</i>
 <i>the feeling of dread?</i>

00:17.400 --> 00:19.100
 <i>I'm not talking about fear.</i>

00:19.100 --> 00:20.200
 <i>Fear is immediate.</i>

00:20.200 --> 00:23.100
 <i>Fear is what k</i>

00:23.600 --> 00:25.200
 <i>A mugger with a gun.</i>

00:25.500 --> 00:27.400
 <i>A stranger in your house.</i>

00:28.000 --> 00:29.800
 <i>I'm talking about dread.</i>

00:31.700 --> 00:33.500
 <i>Dread is persistent.</i>

00:33.500 --> 00:35.200
 <i>It gnaws at you.</i>

00:35.500 --> 00:36.900
 <i>You can't ignore it.</i>

00:37.100 --> 00:39.400
 <i>It just won't go away.</i>

00:42.100 --> 00:43.600
 <i>Because that's what dread is.</i>

00:43.600 --> 00:46.900
 <i>It's worrying about something</i>
 <i>you can't do anything about.</i>

00:47.100 --> 00:48.800
 <i>Dread can affect your job,</i>

00:48.800 --> 00:52.200
 <i>your home, alter your entire</i>
 <i>personality.</i>

00:56.500 --> 00:58.300
Hey, sorry to wake you.

00:58.300 --> 01:01.000
I felt funny leaving
without saying good-bye.

01:01.000 --> 01:03.800
It's so early.
I know.

01:03.900 --> 01:06.900
My ride said he needed
to get in before everybody else.

01:06.900 --> 01:09.300
Your ride?
Yeah.
Remember?

01:09.300 --> 01:12.300
I dropped my car off at the shop
on the way home last night.

01:12.700 --> 01:13.700
Oh, right.

01:13.700 --> 01:15.400
I thought I was driving you.

01:15.400 --> 01:17.100
No, I told you.

01:17.600 --> 01:19.400
I looked through
the company directory and I made

01:19.400 --> 01:22.100
some phone calls-- I got a guy
from work to take me.

01:23.800 --> 01:25.500
What's with the long face?

01:25.600 --> 01:28.600
I don't know.
Funny feeling, like...

01:29.700 --> 01:32.700
Like you're...
I'm supposed to drive you or...

01:33.200 --> 01:35.100
Maybe you're not
supposed to go at all.

01:36.100 --> 01:37.500
You hear that?

01:37.500 --> 01:39.700
Maybe it's the world's
way of telling us

01:39.700 --> 01:41.800
to stay in bed, just...

01:42.300 --> 01:44.500
let a day go by without us.

01:44.700 --> 01:46.900
I'll let you explain
that to my bosses.

01:47.000 --> 01:49.600
Today's the monthly project
management meeting.

01:49.600 --> 01:52.700
But I'm sure they'd be happy
to call it on account of rain.

01:53.700 --> 01:56.000
That's my ride.
Are you sure

01:56.100 --> 01:57.500
you don't want
me to drive you?

01:57.500 --> 02:00.500
I have a funny feeling.
No, it's fine. Really.

02:01.500 --> 02:03.300
If you want to do
something for me,

02:03.300 --> 02:06.400
if it clears, maybe you can
swing by the dry cleaners

02:06.400 --> 02:08.100
and pick up my shirts.

02:08.100 --> 02:09.600
That would be...
(doorbell rings)

02:09.600 --> 02:12.000
Can you grab that?
I'm just going to get my bag.

02:14.000 --> 02:15.900
Hi, uh, I'm Bruce.
I'm here for Joe.

02:15.900 --> 02:17.800
Oh, yeah. Come in, come in.

02:18.100 --> 02:19.900
I'm Allison, I'm Joe's wife.

02:22.400 --> 02:24.100
Hope you brought your ark.

02:27.300 --> 02:29.300
Um, well, let me just...

02:29.300 --> 02:32.100
Uh, check on Joe,
see what he's up to.

02:37.800 --> 02:40.000
Hey, sorry to wake you, but...

02:40.000 --> 02:42.900
You felt funny leaving
without saying good-bye.

02:43.900 --> 02:44.600
Yeah.

02:45.300 --> 02:47.000
I need you to say home.

02:47.900 --> 02:49.000
Honey, that's my ride.

02:49.000 --> 02:51.700
No, I mean it.
I really need you to stay home.

02:51.700 --> 02:53.600
Okay. Can you tell me why?

02:54.000 --> 02:56.400
No. A feeling.

02:56.400 --> 02:58.100
Maybe it's the rain.

02:58.600 --> 03:00.100
Maybe it's the thunder.

03:00.100 --> 03:02.800
Okay, well, the rain
is going to stop,

03:02.800 --> 03:04.300
and the thunder will pass.

03:04.300 --> 03:05.600
I really need to go to work.

03:05.600 --> 03:08.400
The kids really need to go
to school, not to mention...

03:08.400 --> 03:10.900
I know. Your shirts,
the cleaners...

03:10.900 --> 03:12.800
Big meeting. Wish me luck.

03:13.800 --> 03:15.200
Luck...

